<br>
Anyone ever heard of Anne Rice?  Dracula is a one-dimensional, cardboard cut-out compared to ANY of the characters of Anne Rine...<br>
<br>
Okay, I'm slightly biased ... I think Anne Rice is a Goddess -- comparable only to Dianne, Isis, Bjork, Germaine Greer or Jane Morris (anyone heard of Dante Rossetti?), comparable even to  Dottie (perhaps??)...<br>
<br>
If you don't know what I'm talking about, read &quot;Interview with the Vampire&quot;, &quot;Goddess of the Dammed&quot;, &quot;Pandora&quot;, &quot;The Body Thief&quot; etc... infact, checkout any of the Vampire Chronicles.<br>
<br>
So, anyway ... here are my votes:<br>
<br>
The scariest vampire of all time:  Armand (he's too human!)<br>
The sexiest vampire of all time:   Pandora<br>
The most adorable v.o.a. time:   Claudia<br>
The ultimate vampire of all time:  Lestat<br>
<br>
(PS - Yes, I have heard of Bauhaus ... I've never actually HEARD them, but I've got a postcard promoting 'Bela Lugosi's Dead' on my wall -- because my sister sent it to me &amp; it looked cool: does that make me sad??? - pls don't answer that!)<br>
<br>
((PPS - totally, 100% agree with you about Armand, Summers Death -- I only read the book(s) after I saw the film, however I could never place the character in the carriage, in the film, after Louis had destroyed the Theatre etc  - with Armand, for exactly the reasons that you give...thanks for reassuring me that I wasn't just missing something, or being really stupid there!))<br>
<br>
Paul<br>
Powys/ UK<br>
